## Unit 3: Lesson 18 - Improving the Clicker Game

# Background

You probably have many ideas about how the quick double-clicker game could be more fun and challenging. The good news is that over the next few lessons, you will learn how to add some of your ideas by using variables to store information and using conditionals to make decisions.

# Lesson

* Think about the features you would like to add to make a better clicker game.
* Identify the programming elements that would enable the improvements.
* Categorize the programming elements according to their purposes in the game.

